suite.doc:
Robot Framework 7.4.1 Test Standards for Amazon Q
This file defines the authoritative standards for Robot Framework test automation using modern RF 7.4.1 syntax, Browser Library 19.12.3, and RequestsLibrary 0.9.7.
MANDATORY COMPLIANCE: - Use ONLY keywords validated via rf-docs-mcp tools - Enforce modern syntax (VAR, IF/ELSE, FOR, TRY/EXCEPT) - Implement Page Object Model for UI tests - Follow Gherkin patterns in test cases - Ensure test independence and stability
FORBIDDEN PATTERNS: - Legacy keywords (Run Keyword If, Set Test Variable) - Fixed Sleep statements - Hardcoded values in test cases - Linear scripting without abstraction
